The paper introduces a deep learning model for de novo peptide sequencing, which involves analyzing mass spectrometry data to identify tumor-specific neoantigens. This falls under the intersection of bioinformatics and machine learning, which is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.BIO (Bioinformatics). The model uses a combination of order invariant network structure and recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, these categories are also likely to be relevant.
